Suspended National Chairman of the All Progressives Congress, APC, Adams Oshiomhole, on Saturday reacted to the dissolution of the party’s National Working Committee, NWC. Oshiomhole said he has accepted the decision of the party’s National Executive Council, NEC. Addressing journalists on Saturday, Oshiomhole also disclosed that he has directed his lawyers to withdraw all court cases. The suspended National Chairman assured that he remains loyal to the party and President Muhammadu Buhari. “Loyalty is put to test when the going is tough,” Oshiomhole said. Details later…